16/10/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Economy and Finance Minister Nikos Christodoulakis said Wednesday (15 October) that Greece fully supports the Pan-European network projects in the energy and telecommunications sectors. 
He explained that these projects are of huge significance in Southern Europe where networks in these sectors are underdeveloped. 
Christodoulakis added that Greece would promote new programmes for small and medium-sized enterprises at the upcoming informal EU meeting on Pan-European networks. 
(ANA - 15/10/03)
